Oct 27 2009 	Great value would recommend to friends and family.	I booked a four night stay Thursday thru Sunday at the Sahara Casino before I read the many reviews on this website. After reading many reviews, I was somewhat nervous about what to expect when we arrived. One review I read suggested that we request the Tangiers tower since it had been remodeled and more up to date than the other towers. Upon arrival we waited 15 minutes in line and was helped by a very friendly front desk. There is a $6 mandatory fee per night regardless of what you booked in advance. We went ahead and requested the Tangier tower with no problem or additional cost. I don't know what people expect of a room when you pay 50$ per night. The room was clean and comfortable. It was like staying at a Best Western. Overall the casino was not as run down a reviewers made it sound. It was a very good value for the price. If your looking for luxury book at the Bellagio.	
