Oct 1 2009 	Good location and value for money	I stayed here nine days and felt it was a good hotel. As for the location, it was excellent, near the top of the strip, within a 15 walk of the Fashion Show Mall to the south or the Stratosphere to the north, and with easy access by car to the Interstate 15 highway (around a mile to the west). I don't understand how people can complain that the Sahara is far from everything! Don't you have legs for walking? And there's the Monorail station right next to the hotel, though it is expensive to use compared to the Deuce bus which runs down the Strip.As for cleanliness, it was fine. Alright, there were a few small stains on the carpet in the room, but the hotel is basically very clean. Of course, it would be cleaner still if management were to have sufficient courage to ban smoking everywhere, rather than simply think about how much money they'd like to make (banning smoking would lead to them making less money). Smoking is only allowed in the casino area, but customers walk everywhere with their cigarettes, even to areas where it's not permitted like near to the reception. Banning smoking would be the first step to turn around this hotel and the numerous complaints about it being dirty. The hotel is simply the reflection of the people staying there, after all!Room service was pretty good, and the bathroom was regularly cleaned daily. There was some mildew round the edge of the bath, but nothing to worry about.I don't know how much I paid for the room as I came on a package with flight included, but it can't have been much. The room was spacious. I'd say to potential customers not to be put off by the numerous fusspots posting to this site for whom nothing would be enough - you can't get a five-star hotel for a budget rate!	
