Jun 14 2009 	It is what it is....but not as bad as some of these reviews.	Put it in perspective - it is old, worn and could use a touch of updating. But, it's also a great way to do a vacation on a budget when you don't want to spend $150 or $200 a night. It was clean, the staff was friendly for the most part and at less than $30 a night, it's hard to beat. It is off the beaten path - if you rent a car or want to use the monorail, it's fine. If you want to walk, forget it. If you have a choice, stay in the Tangiers towers - a little newer than the Alexandria and not as dated. Unfortuntately, the previous reviewer is correct - the two nicer restaurants are closed through June due to the slowness of the economy. But, we had decent meals in both the Caravan Cafe and the NASCAR cafe. Now, if you are willing to spend more $, then there are better places to stay, but I figure Vegas is gonna take enough of my money, I might as well keep the rooms to a minimum.......heck, how much time are you going to spend in the room anyway? Oh, and one last thing - the pool here is very nice.	
