Feb 16 2009 	Can't wait to go back	We just returned from a 3 night stay at Sahara for which the total cost was $150.00. Our room was on the 15th floor with a balcony. The view was of the Sahara sign the Stratosphere and, best of all, the mountains.. Our room was large and very clean with the exception of the sheer curtains beneath the drapes. They were very dirty and tore when I tried to pull them back. I notified housekeeping and they were removed immediately. The first morning, I discovered the hairdryer did not work and within 15 minutes, a new one was installed. The Caravan Cafe was excellent as was The House of Lords. (not so much, the buffet.) The casino is smalled than the newer hotels, but it is clean and the slots are loose. You never have to look for a cocktail waitress. They are very accomodating. The 60's style band that played every night was a lot of fun.The perks you get with the player's club card are terrific and the comp points paid for all of our meals. The last stop on the monorail is at the Sahara and you can travel to the other end of the strip in 15 minutes. The hotel is old and somewhat worn, but it is clean, the staff is very friendly and the food was good. We definitely got our moneys worth and then some. I can't wait to return.	
