Jan 9 2009 	This is NOT a BAD hotel!!!	Ok...so I booked my reservation based on 2 things: #1: Money and #2: I wanted a hotel with a 1 night minimum stay on New Years Eve. Sahara is the only one that has a 1 night minimum stay. The price was SO VERY reasonable for us. We live 4 hours away and I've never been to Vegas and wanted to spend New Years Eve there. Every other hotel was HUNDREDS of dollars per night and wanted at least a 2 night stay. No way could we afford that...in this economy! After I booked this stay, somehow I was directed to this site. I have to say that I was SCARED out of my mind after reading some of the reviews. Bed bugs? Filthy rooms? Bad customer Service? Oh my!!! I almost cancelled my trip. But I got to thinking...You can't please everyone and I know there are people out there that are going to complain even if it were a 5 star hotel. Some people just live to complain about everything. So I decided to go anyway. What's to lose? Not money...I got a great deal. I've stayed in some bad places that were suppose to be good before. If this place turned out to be bad, I'd chalk it up to an experience. I have to say, my experience was GREAT! We got there at 2:30 on New Years Eve. No long lines to check in. They were quick AND very friendly. They even gave me a room with a view so my 5 year old daughter could see the Fireworks since we knew we wouldn't be out in the crowds with her. We DIDN'T even ask. They are that thoughtful. And since we told her it was our first time there, she gave us free dinners at the buffet. We didn't use them, but it was a nice gesture anyway. Not a single problem with checking in like others have stated. And while I'm on it, there were no problems or long lines checking out either. There were no hidden charges or screw ups on our bill either. So to recap, Checking IN/OUT was great! The hotel was NOT DIRTY. The lobby, casino, stores, cafes,etc...ALL CLEAN and FRIENDLY! AND an employee even gave my husband a $50 voucher to use in the slots or whatever. We just cashed it in! They just GAVE us $50! I've never just been handed $50 before. They didn't even make us use it in the casino. It was ours to do with what we wanted. We weren't the only one's getting the vouchers either. He had a large stack in his hands. Back to cleanliness. Our room was average. We got what we paid for. I compare it to a Days Inn, Ramada Inn, etc. Nothing elaborate. But it was Clean. No mis-matched carpet, no peeling paint, no dirty sheets, no dirty bathroom and certainly...NO BED BUGS. It was CLEAN! The beds were very comfortable too! And the view was FANTASTIC! However, I do agree that the furniture is outdated. But it added to the place I think. It probably is the original furniture that was used in the day of Frank Sinatra and the Beatles and all the other well know celebrities that stayed there. But it was all very well taken care of and I have no complaints about it at all. The linens and drapery and towels were all modern. There was no cigarette smell or anything. In fact, the only time I saw any mis-matched carpet or dirty areas was in the elevators. But you have to understand...how many people go in and out of there in a day? Thousands and thousands. And some of those people are extremely intoxicated, carrying their drinks and spilling. There are kids dropping things and let's face it...our shoes are not clean people. Another great thing about this place is you can get on the Monorail right there IN the hotel. It'll take you down the strip. But we walked. It's not a bad walk. Even if you're overweight or have asthma, it's still a very do-able walk. My 5 year old walked the entire strip and back again and it didn't phase her at all. This is a great Hotel for the money. And lets face it, we all are watching our money now a days. It was clean and hospitable and I would recommend it to anyone if they asked.	
