Dec 31 2008 	Stay here to save money	I was actually surprised, and happy to end up with a large, very clean room. For my purposes, a business trip during Memorial Day weekend in 2008, I felt I made a good choice. I was on a budget, and needed a cheap room with easy access to the Sands Convention Center.The most important details I learned while staying at the Sahara.1. The casino is small and unpopular. 2. The buffet is cheap and unpopular. 3. The pool is adequate, and everyone I met was there for the same reason I was there - discounted rates advertised on Expedia.4.Don't trust Expedia, I was charged an extra &quot;daily room rate&quot; on top of Expedia's final charge, and later that year my Uncle's reservation at the hotel booked through Expedia wasn't even honored. BOOK DIRECT ONLY.5. The Sahara is the last stop on the Monorail, making it truly the last stop on the Strip. If you have to choose between the Sahara and Stratosphere, stay at the Sahara. 6. Plan to take the Monorail to where the action is every day and night, stay at the Sahara to sleep.7. They are actually not always the cheapest in regards to good location. For 2009, I'm considering the Imperial Palace and Excalibur because they are closer to the center, and have good rates.8. Wi-fi internet access for your laptop computer is not free.	
