Aug 2 2008 	Adequate with long lines @ check in 	Stayed two nights during the week with an extremely low rate booked at the hotels web site after receiving an email alerting me to a special price on the rooms. Sign up at the hotel web site for their emails.Yes, this hotel is at the far north of the strip, but it's got a monorail stop just out the door and up an escalator. Also, two bus stops, one in front for the &quot;deuce&quot; and one behind for the regular buses. You can bus it to the hotel for $1.25 from the airport or downtown if you do a little research. You can also walk to the Wynn/Venetian area. It's 1.2 miles and the route is not usually crowded like it is further down the strip.Rooms are adequate. Got a standard room this time. Previously have stayed in their suites which are a good value compared to others on the strip. My room this time could have been cleaner. It should have been vacuumed better. Linens and bathroom were clean though.I arrived around 10am and was asked to come back to check in when rooms would be available. Fair enough. I checked my bags and went to play poker. Returned in mid afternoon and the line to check in was about 60 feet long with only 3 stations open at the desk. Decided to go get a bite to eat at the buffet and discovered it was due to open at 4:30pm. Also noticed that with my &quot;club sahara&quot; card I could get the buffet for about 1/2 price so I decided to waste some time and come back later. At 4:45pm the line for the buffet was easily 100 feet long with no apparent movement. Went to McDonalds across the street. Came back and the line at check in was the same length. Played poker until 11pm. Check in line at 11pm was gone. Check in staff were courteous.Long story short - great prices, adequate rooms, clean bathrooms, airconditioning worked well, but plan on standing in long lines at times. A fair distance from the heart of the strip but it has great options for getting there via monorail and bus.Will stay there agai