Jul 24 2008 	Basic Accomodations; Great Price	The Sahara is an older property, and is definitely showing its age. The rooms are very basic -- think 1970's Howard Johnson's. But they were clean and reasonably comfortable. The A/C was only marginally effective -- had to keep the blinds closed to keep the room tolerably cool. Just as well. Not much of a view from my room. The service was marginal, at best. Long lines at check-in, and only 2 clerks working. They are clearly understaffed, even at peak hours. Everyone was pleasant, though.The casino is decent, but the poker room definitely needs an upgrade. It is crowded and very smoky, even though smoking is not actually allowed at the tables (I am a smoker myself, and even I found it unpleasant). The property is off the strip, so you have to take a cab anywhere. There were usually cabs available, but not always. Had to wait for the bellman to call us a cab at checkout. A minor inconvenience, but not something you would experience at any of the major properties on the strip. All that being said, the room rates were excellent, and it was a decent value. Don't plan your honeymoon or a romantic weekend there -- this is NOT a resort property. But if you just want a place to crash, and would rather save your money for the tables, it's definitely worth a look.	
Jul 22 2008	Sahara was great!	Great hotel to stay if on a budged. My overall experience was good. Well worth the money. The room was clean and comfy, the only bad thing is the carpet is stained and the furniture was old, but you get what you pay for so I didn't care. It had a excellent access bridge to the monorail right next to the lobby and a liquor store right in the lobby with cold brewskies. The pool scene was nice and refreshing. It sure beats staying at roach motel for the same price. My only complaint would be the buffet, it was nasty and dull, it made me sick. Just avoid it, the Caravan Cafe is really good.	
Jul 20 2008 	not fancy but nice	Stayed on a Tuesday thru Saturday. 7/15 - 7/19.There were three of us staying in one room. Not real fancy. The furniture is old but the beds were comfortable and clean. They don't give you a lot of extras, but it's inexpensive and we usually bring our own. They do have a fridge you can rent for $10.90 a day. Comes in handy for leftovers and drinks. The monorail is real handy for getting closer to the glitz. The pool is nice but, doesn't open or get any sun until 9 a.m. Only ate one meal in the hotel, breakfast at Caravan's , in the casino. Tasted good and was about average in price. Also at at the IHOP, about a bloke down the blvd. Fast service and just like every other IHOP. We were looking for a quite clean place to stay with easy access to the more glitzy properties and we got it.	
