Jul 18 2008 	Don't stay here	My wife and I stayed at the Sahara Casino Hotel from July 14th to 17th. We read some of the reviews after we booked and were going to cancel but it was after the 72-hour cancellation penalty before we realized our mistake! The first thing you see upon arriving is the run down garage with trash and broken beer bottles. The elevators are also rundown; the arrows that indicate weather the elevator is going up or down don’t work. Then the elevator’s door open, finally, and you see more trash, then to top it off the fans are broken and it so hot inside the elevator you can’t wait to get out even when the temperature outside was 105. Self-parking is above the third floor we finally found a spot on the fifth.Check-in is at 3 p.m.; we arrived at 4:20 to find a line that was so long I couldn’t believe it was for check-in. The hotel only had two clerks to check in new guests. We waited for 55 minutes before it was our turn.The hotel elevators are also run down and feel like they are going to break down at anytime. Our room was well used and worn out, it should have been remodeled along time ago. The beds were pretty soft but we slept ok on them. The room was a little stuffy when we arrived so we turned on the air conditioner and it was the loudest thing I have ever heard. While we were awake the noise was livable but at night I had to turn it off to sleep, then the room would get stuffy again.I only ate one time in the buffet and it was horrible, the worst I have ever eaten at, and I’m not a picky eater I’ll eat almost anything. One more thing that was disappointing was that the pool was closed at 7 P.M. and they forced you to leave.We only paid $35.00 a night + tax + a $6.00 resort fee. You get what you pay for; I would gladly pay more for a better hotel and will in the future. BUYERS BEWARE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!There were two high points about staying here, first, the Las Vegas Monorail has a station at the back of the hotel so it’s really easy to get to, second, the public bus “the Duce” is also right out in front on the Strip and easy to get to.	
