Jun 23 2008 	Not bad; watch for hidden fees	Arrived late afternoon at the hotel; took about 20 minutes to get to the check-in counter with all the other travelers checking in. Staff was very pleasant and was soon in a nice-enough room. No coffee maker, no fridge, but the queen beds were comfortable and there were extra pillows, an appreciated little extra, as well as plenty of towels. Bathroom was clean and roomy. Rooms are quiet; the view of the Stratosphere and the old downtown area out the north side was picture-worthy. Went to the 9:30 Roseanne Barr show (she's a hoot) and enjoyed a quiet night's sleep. Lots of 70's vintage black and white celebrity photos throughout the casino shopping areas and restaurants. Checking out this morning, I was hit with a mandatory $6.00 &quot;Daily Facility Fee&quot; that no one told me about. Clerical staff apologized but would not take it off of the bill, even though I didn't even use the telephone or pool or anything. I have submitted to my booking agency for a refund, but will probably not stay at the Sahara again, only due to this non-negotable hidden fee.	
