Jun 23 2008 	Good for the Price	First time to Vegas. Booked the Sahara Hotel based on the the cheapest available Strip Hotel. We weren't looking for anything fancy, just a place that we can base ourselves in. Great that its the last stop of the Las Vegas Monorail. Easy to get all the way down to the end of the Strip if you're willing to pay the $9 for two people. Has a Deuce bus stop right outside. The rooms were nice and clean, however the mattress had a really noticable stain on the fabric that wouldn't have been noticed unless we had lifted the sheets. Other than that the rooms were nice enough for the price.Really hard to get a hold of the main desk during the day but they were helpful once you reached someone. The pool was small but clean. The casino isn't exactly what you would stay at the hotel for but had plenty of tables that offered lessons throughout the day, which was nice for beginners.All in all, for the price you get what you pay for. If you're going to Las Vegas to hang around the main parts of the Strip, it's probably best to fork over a few more dollars and stay in a hotel more central to the action. If you're willing to pay for the Deuce/Monorail/Cab/Bus it's a decent place to stay.	
