Jun 18 2008	Value on the Strip	After reading all the reviews, I decided to stay at the Sahara for one night for the following reasons:- As a previous reviewer noted, the Deluxe rooms in the Tangiers tower were the most recently renovated. At $10 more than the basic room, it is the best value and we found no fault with the room we were given. I specifically called the hotel before booking to ensure that if I booked a Deluxe room, we would be in that tower. The room was clean and odor-free as to be expected from a non-smoking room.- The pool may not have been as large, but it was very clean, and not as crowded as other places. It was also very easy to access straight through the lobby.- As a budget traveler to Vegas, I freuqently stay at the Motel 6 on Tropicana. On a weekday night, the Sahara offered comparable prices to the Motel 6 and was definitely 10 times better.- While some people may complain that it is at the far side of the Strip, I always recommend people take Paradise Road if driving to get anywhere quickly. It runs parallel to Las Vegas Blvd. right behind the Sahara and all the other hotels, WITHOUT the traffic.	
