May 20 2008	Acceptable for the price	We had stayed at the Sahara in 2004, and to be truthful, all that had changed in that time was the date on the calendar. It was old then, but even older now. However, if you can get a decent room rate via one of the online promotions, don't dismiss it. The Sahara is really not all bad, just make sure you get a 'deluxe' room. I've never stayed in a standard room, but having stayed in the deluxe rooms both times, this is about the minimum standard that's acceptable these days. The deluxe rooms are a good size, and the ones higher up in the Tunis Tower are better (according to the staff). Check-in was fine for us, but we did see some awfully long queues. You will need some earplugs though - the doors slam really loudly if inconsiderate guests leave them to self-close. The clientele is better than some other budget hotels on the strip, with most guests being older (and therefore quieter). Would I stay there again? No, I would either save up more money, or stay for less time, in the Venetian, which is truly magnificent. Vegas on a budget? Yes, if the price is right.	
