noses at guests...but not at the SaharaI didnt have a long check in wait, but I did arrive around 1am on an early Wednesday morning....however, I did see some huge lines during my stay...I would suggest either checking your stuff with the bell desk and messing around until a later time or just be ready to wait it out.After I had visited nearly every hotel and casino on the strip and downtown, I have to say, the Saraha is by far one of the cleanest...the bathrooms in even the nicest places seemed to be filthy. I wouldnt even use the facilites at the NYNY or the Flamingo....bleh.Where else on the strip can you find a room for under $40/night, right on the monorail, clean rooms, helpful staff and decent food?? I have to say, for the naysayers....might wanna move on down the strip and pay 3-5 times as much for the flash and dash that the Sahara doesnt have and leave them to what they're doing...I dont see much wrong with it...course I'm just an average Jane...living an average kinda lifestyle.	
