Mar 20 2008 	Hotel in need of refurbishment	We stayed here for 3 nights in January 2008. Although the room was comfortable, it was in need of refurbishment. The carpet was stained and the bed clothes had holes in them. The buffet restaurant is excellent and very good value for money, especially if you join Club Sahara as you get a discount. The hotel is now somewhat remote from the rest of the strip, but there is an excellent cheap bus service (The Duece) which runs the whole length of the strip and goes to Fremont Street in downtown Las Vegas. Best value is the all day pass - you can hop on/off the bus all day and can buy the pass on the bus. If you are doing Las Vegas on a budget, this is an adequate hotel, but if you can afford it, stay more centrally.	
