Mar 15 2008	Love Sahara	I really like the Sahara. I've stayed there several times over the years. This hotel is not in the &quot;heart&quot; of the Strip ... but the Strip seems to be branching out longer and longer and the Sahara is certainly still &quot;in the action.&quot; This hotel has a great pool, nice rooms and good food. I'm not a big &quot;buffet&quot; person ... but the buffet at Sahara is pretty good. There is also a pretty good &quot;steakhouse&quot; and a breakfast coffee shop. One great thing about the Sahara is that it's a Las Vegas Monorail stop ... so if you want to venture out you can catch the Las Vegas monorail and get to virtually any of the other areas of the Strip without trouble or too much expense. It's also an easy bus ride to Fremont Street which is alot of fun and much more of the &quot;old fashioned&quot; Las Vegas. There are often great free concerts there and some fun older casinos. One other really nice thing about the Sahara is that there is a good store kitty-corner to the hotel. It's billed as a big souvenior shop, but it also has liquor and mixers etc. And you can get some things there that you might need. Sahara doesn't really offer &quot;top tier&quot; shows ... but I DID go to one show there that was really good. Again, buy tickets to other shows and ride the monorail to them. This hotel is a little older although it's been updated and is totally comfortable and nice. I've never had a problem with cleanliness or service. I think it's a great value compared to alot of the other &quot;mega hotels&quot; etc. Believe it or not I'm NOT a gambler ... I tend to go to Vegas with friends that like that more than I do .. but Sahara has a nice casino area and I HAVE enjoyed plunking a few quarters or nickel's in their machines. There is one particularly fun section that is 60's themed and the dealers wear tie dye and there is 60's music and it's actually pretty fun. If you are into NASCAR they have alot of that and also a really great roller coaster ... it's short in duration but pretty thrilling and the last time I went on it you got two rides for about 10 bucks. There is also a good lounge with music ... usually when I've been there it's kind of &quot;bluesy&quot; type music but it's kind of relaxing and I often wind up going there and listening to the music while my friends are out in the casino gambling. All in all I love the Sahara ... it's one of my favorite places to stay in Vegas. It seems like it has a mix of nostalgia .. kind of like what you would think the &quot;old Vegas&quot; would be like, but still has the modern amenities and all.	
