Feb 27 2008 	Cheap for a reason	I'll do pros first to not scare everyone awayPRO:Cheap - 4 nights in a standard 2 double bed room for $315.On the stip with a Monorail Station - you can get all the way to the other end of the strip in 15 minutes on this.Pretty fun rollercoaster.Hair dryer, iron, ironing board.Double bed was short but comfortable mattress and nice pillows.The Grind Coffee Shop - nice quick coffee service - as good as Starbucks though not as many options.No Bedbugs - believe me I know where to check and what to look for - this was just in my room - check your own if you stay here.CON:1. Shabby - I have never seen so much rust in a hotel room. Peeling wallpaper, don't even look at the bottom of the doorjambs in the bathroom, 2. Window cranks broken (yes the windows do open - but good luck getting them closed again).3. My personal favorite - no heating or AC control - only a little plastic sign above a dial that allows you to controll the speed of a fan that states &quot;This does not controll heating or air conditioning, only air flow, temperature is dertermined by outside temperature&quot; It was freezing in our room. Can't imagine what it would be like in hotter months.4. Good luck getting the room you reserve - &quot;Oh, you wanted a non-smoking room with a king bed? All we have is non-smoking with 2 double beds&quot; What is the point of paying for a room in advance?!? My husband is 6'1&quot; and got to sleep with his feet hanging off the end of the bed. A pro of this is that we took the blanket off the second bed to keep from freezing at night.5. Charge for internet access - even standard Motel 8s have free internet.6. The $4 fee per day they charge you upon check in - I was way too tired to even argue about this - I'm sure they count on that.7. This may be my fault - Most casinos don't take change in their machines anymore - but I don't get to Vegas much and didn't know this. I save all my change for a little gambling money but when I got here I found out that they can't even exchange it - I was told to go to a local grocery store where they have a Coinstar - nice.8. The Caravan - they managed to take all the flavor out of the food but not the Vegas style prices - waitstaff was friendly but it was painfully slow service.OK - end all be all - It was cheap and I know everyone says you get what you pay for - but I feel this was worth less than what I paid. Would I stay here again - No. Would I recommend it to anybody on anything other than the tightest shoestring budget - No.If you stay here get Monorail tickets and only use this place to sleep and shower.	
