Jan 28 2008 	Not horrible very basic	Stayed here 1/25-1/27 for a total of $100. I only booked a couple of hours before check-in and expected the worst after reading the reviews, but we were just looking for a cheap place to get away from family, and this was the second cheapest in town, including off-strip!We arrived at about 11 p.m., and there were only two ladies working the check-in desk, so it took at least half an hour to get to the front of the line. Once we were there, we were checked in quickly and paid the $4 per day hidden fee in cash.We stayed in the Tangiers tower, right by check-in, and the room looked exactly like the photos shown a few reviews down from this one. I expected it to stink or have a dirty damp feeling, but this was probably one of the most scentless places I've ever stayed. No dirty scent, no clean scent, no scent at all. Everything was very clean other than a little rust in the bath.The one problem I had with the room was that it was completely lacking in information. It didn't have any of those Las Vegas magazines listing attractions or even a brochure showcasing the hotel's features that so many other places have. There were a bunch of menus from local pizza delivery places on our floor when we arrived, so we figured that was the Sahara's replacement for room service. After having our room cleaned, the menus were gone, so we called down to have some more sent up and were given the runaround being transferred to different departments. Finally found out the hotel doesn't distribute them, and they do actually have room service, so someone from housekeeping ran a room service menu up to us. I really don't understand why this wasn't available in the room in the first place.We did end up using room service which was delivered quickly, and everything in our order was made correctly.We also tried the cafe and buffet, both of which were average. I actually liked the buffet very much, but I only ate cold items like salad and fruit, while my boyfriend ate a lot of the cooked dishes and hated them, complaining they were cold or undercooked. We both felt awful after eating there though. There was also no one to pick up our dirty plates.Overall, the Sahara was clean and a decent place to stay for the price, but I'd never choose it for a special occasion. Also, since we live here we weren't really using it to have close access to the popular Vegas sites, so I didn't have any complaints about location. However, some might since it is very far north strip, but it does have monorail access which will take you to center and south strip. Good luck!	
