Oct 4 2007 	NEVER again	We only had to stay at the Sahara for one night and thankfully we were leaving at 4 am the next morning for our flight. I would not recommend this hotel to anyone. It seems like they don't even care about the hotel rooms almost as if they know sometime soon someone will buy the hotel and tear it down. We checked into the Tangiers Tower which by the description on the Sahara website this was a &quot;deluxe&quot; room. There was NOTHING deluxe about this room. - The elevators to get to your room are scary (buttons for floors missing/old/door doesn't close all the way). - When you get off on your floor it appears as though you've stepped back in time to the '70's and are blown away with the smell. We were on a non smoking floor but at that point smokey smell would have been welcomed. - Room was terrible. Everything is old and appeared as if it had been heavily used and abused. The beds were higher on the foot of the bed and sloped down as you got closer to the wall.P.S. the room keys are just plain white.....just white! They don't even care to print the hotel name on them.....nothing! - Laminated &quot;Safety &amp; Security&quot; card is scary. Don't get me wrong, other hotels have security steps but they don't lay them out for you to read as soon as you check into your room. Also, no hotel clearly has ever displayed the fact that you can call the front desk for a Sharps container so you can safely dispose of your NEEDLES! I'm almost thinking that they are not referring to needles needed for medical reasons after looking at the surroundings. - Area is also poor. There is nothing close that you really need to walk and see. The Statosphere is within walking distance though.I would strongly recommend that anyone thinking about staying here take 10 extra minutes and visit the website of a few other hotels in the center of the strip instead. Treasure Island is centrally located and would be considered luxury compared to the Sahara. You can get pretty good deals there and you would have a much more amazing Vegas experience there. The center of the strip is a night and day difference compared to the end by Sahara. I can understand now when people stay at that end and then tell me that they really didn't enjoy the trip to Vegas. The center of the strip has the Fashionshow Mall and wonderful places to eat there (Maggiano's; RA sushi; Capital Grille), you are right across the street from Wynn and Venetian (Must See), right down from Ceasar's and the Forum Shops and very close to Margaritaville. There is WAY more to do and see here and better walking enviroment as well. I say the Sahara is a 1 star hotel and if that is what your looking for great, if you expect a decent hotel for your money (no matter how good your deal is) then do not book here. Take your money somewhere else.	
