ly. (2) Nascar CAFÉ: Bartender didn’t know who won the race! Now Come On!! Do Overs: a short list of things we would DEFINITELY go back just to see. Out side Harrah’s is a small court of vendors a bar and a stage which had entertainment on it all day and the bartenders really can flare! its entertainment itself! Again at Harrah’s…. the dueling piano bar. $5 cover-drinks were average and both the men and women were great entertainers. They had to make Boo Coo Cash that night! Great Job! The hotel itself is VERY CROWDED. Imperial ? or Palace Station (I think): $1 Michelob’s, we commented on the bartenders shirt and he directed to us where to buy it and some other great souvenirs. Beside it being quite chilly at night and our hockey team losing in a shoot out ? (Go Av’s!) our trip was a blast! Cant wait till next years hockey game. Will definitely stay at the Sahara and next time were taking 2 more girls with us. Thanks to everyone at the Sahara.(Though most never heard of this web site) I would definitely recommend this hotel! ****	
